VDevan Drone, the Indian classical fusion music group, enthralled the audience at Shilparamam here recently with their unique Carnatic music with a western touch, blending Hindustani with Irish Music and more.  The orchestra comprised of young musicians  Vasudevan on the violin, Dronendra Phani Kumar (flute), Kalyana Raman ( mridangam), Surabhi Phani Bhushan (ghatam), Pavan (rhythm pads) and Arun Balakrishna (guitar). The ensemble opened the recital with theVaataapiganapatim (Hamsadhwani, Adi). The high speedSwarakalpanason both violin and flute that they included during the ending of this item left the audience spellbound. TheEnglish Notecomposed by Sri Madhurai Mani Iyer inraga Shankarabharanamwith few alien notes was the next item perfectly presented by Devan Drone to give the western music feel to the audience. . , where they teach music to various aspirants.Bottom Template Starts
